value: the river still open in the middle. about 1/2 past 10 pm [10:30pm] motion of higher clouds from nw to south west, velocity 5
the same weather as yesterday. at 1/2 past 10 pm [10:30pm] a large halo round the moon of a  yellowish colur. motion of higher clouds from north to south east. velocity 4
a few flakes of snow fell this morning about 1/2 past six [6:30am]. the greatest degree of cold during the night 24°
begun to snow at 3pm. turned to rain at 4pm. still raining at 10pm. small rain
begun to snow at 2am. continued snowing until 1pm. depth of fallen snow  then 2 inches. snowed again a little this evening
at 1am the river a mass of floating ice. at 2pm half frozen over
still floating ice in the middle of the river
begun to snow heavily at 7am. continued so for an hour. then snowed lightly until 11am
very mild weather, snow meltingon the ground and dripping like rain from the roofs of the houses. a very heavy fall of snow this afternoon

the river entirely frozen over opposite the fort, but a little higher up, within sight, still an open space. about 10pm amount of cloudiness 8. motion of higher clouds from south east to n. velocity 3
the river altogether frozen over, crossed over it this morning for the first time. beautifully clear last night, not a cloud seen
thawing all day
a thick heavy fog this morning.cleared away fradually  until 8am when it disappeared altogether. began to snow at 10pm
continued snowing all day. at intervals large heavy flakes,  ceased altogether at 3pm. depth of fallen snow 6 inches
clear starry night last night. very early this morning a halo round the moonl the outer rim of a dark colour, the inner rim yellowish colour.
the greatest degree of cold during the night, past -30°
about 10pm a very heavy mist; i could almost call it small rain, but being so perfectly dark nothing can be distinguished

drizzling rain for about an hour this forenoon. began to clear up at 4pm quite clear by 9pm. at 10pm a dense mist: cleared in half an hour. aurora of a light colour. stretching from north to east. thawing all day
at 10pm small drizzling rain for half an hour. a dense fog after it. cleared up about 5am [on the] 28th
a slight fall of snow, small flakes, for about a quarter of an hour from 3pm to 3:15pm

a dense fog this moring, partially cleared up by 8am. hung over the woods until snow fell at 5pmbut it disappeared, still cloud at 10 1/2 pm [10:30pm] only two stars visible but very dim. snow which fell this evening very small and round
snowing from 6:30am to 9pm, interrupted snow, small flakes
snowed lightly for 15 minutes today, small snow
small snow again the same as yesterday
interrupted snow from 2pm. still snowing and blowing at 10pm. cannot say when it ceased
10pm the coldest night we had yet. clear and starry. no aurora
10:30pm. a large halo round the moon. very faint pale colour. the greatest degree of cold during the night. frost -40°
the greatest degree of cold during the night frost -41°. snowed a little this afternoon. very small snow
the greatest degree of cold last night -46°. a dense fog this morning, cleared away by 7am
the greatest degree of cold last night [illegible]. another dense fog this morning, cleared away by 8am
fine clear sky in the morning. about 9am. a north [illegible] accompanied with heavy mist, followed a short time by snow. very small flakes. cleared up again at 4pm. fine starry night no haze
snow at intervals the whole forenoon. small snow
a few flakes of small snow falling at intervals the whole forenoon

snowed heavily for about an hour, then interrupted snow the rest of the time . turned out calm and clear by 2pm, calm the whole afternoon. at 9pm a storm of wind arose (a soft wind) can scarcely distinguish from what quarter in the night has turned out dar as near as i can tell from the north east
at 9pm a very heavy fall of snow. large flat flakes
cloudy in the morning. began to clear up at 8, at 10am a [illegible] sun, brighter on the east side of the [illegible] the faintest on the west side faded away first
hail in the early part of the morning, followed by snow. large heavy flakes
snowing again all day but interrupted. small snow
beautiful red sky at sunrise to the east and south, in an hour's time the sky entirely overcast. snowing very very heavily the whole afternoon, and blowing strong and drifting in the evening
snowing the whole forenoon but small light snow
slight interrupted snow
a slight fall of snow. the snow dripping off the houses like rain at 2pm
